    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In addition, they received four other cities, along with the villages
        around them: Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Simeon\u2019s territory included all the cities and villages as far
        south as the town of Baalath Beer, which is also known as Ramah in the Negeb. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Tribal Land of Zebulun'
      title: The Tribal Land of Zebulun
      number: 9
      content: "The families of Simeon received their inheritance from Judah\u2019s
        share of land because Judah\u2019s portion exceeded what they needed. So
        the inheritance of the families of Simeon was within the territory of Judah.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:9
        content: "  Simeon\u2019s portion of land was scattered throughout the territory
          of Judah, fulfilling Jacob\u2019s prophecy (see  ). See also  .    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The families of the tribe of Zebulun received the third assignment
        of land. Their boundary reached as far southeast as the city of Sarid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Going west, it ran to Maralah, touched Dabbesheth, and extended to
        the stream near Jokneam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In the other direction, the boundary line went east to the border
        of Chisloth-Tabor, and from there to Daberath and Japhia; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'then it continued east of Gath-Hepher, [[COMMENT(0)]] Eth Kazin,
        Rimmon, and turned toward Neah. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:13
        content: '  Gath-Hepher (three miles northeast of Nazareth) was the birthplace
          of the prophet Jonah. See  .    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The northern boundary of Zebulun passed Hannathon and ended at the
        valley of Iphtah El. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Their land encompassed twelve cities, including Kattath, Nahalal,
        Shimeon, [[COMMENT(0)]] Iralah,  and Bethlehem.   '
      comments:
      - number: 19:15
        content: "  Or \u201CShimron.\u201D See  ;  .      Or \u201CIdalah.\u201D     
          This is not the famous Bethlehem south of Jerusalem. This Bethlehem was
          a town about seven and a half miles (twelve kilometers) west of Nazareth.
          See  .    "
    - name: '16: The Tribal Land of Issachar'
      title: The Tribal Land of Issachar
      number: 16
      content: "Zebulun\u2019s families inherited all these towns and their villages."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The families of the tribe of Issachar received the fourth assignment
        of land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18-21: '
      title: 
      number: 18-21
      content: Their inheritance includedJezreel, Kesulloth, Shunem, Hapharaim, Shion,
        Anaharath,Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez, Remeth, En Gannim, En Haddah, and Beth
        Pazzez.
      comments: []
    - name: '18-21: '
      title: 
      number: 18-21
      content: Their inheritance includedJezreel, Kesulloth, Shunem, Hapharaim, Shion,
        Anaharath,Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez, Remeth, En Gannim, En Haddah, and Beth
