    - name: '49-51: '
      title: 
      number: 49-51
      content: "All the people of Israel gathered in front of the tabernacle [[COMMENT(0)]]
        at Shiloh so that Eleazar the priest, Joshua, and the leaders of the tribes
        could divide all the land west of the Jordan River. They used lots to find
        out how <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> wanted them to divide the land. When
        they finished dividing the land into its regions, the Israelites gave their
        warrior-chief, Joshua son of Nun, his inheritance. As <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        had instructed, they gave him the city he requested\u2014Timnath Serah  in
        the Ephraimite hill country. So he built up the city and lived there."
      comments:
      - number: "19:49\u201351"
        content: "  Or \u201Ctent of meeting [assembly].\u201D        means \u201Can
          extra portion.\u201D It is taken from the verb  , meaning \u201Cto count\u201D
          or \u201Cto assign\u201D and the noun  , meaning \u201Cexcess.\u201D The
          Israelites, following God\u2019s instructions, gave Joshua what he longed
          for: an extra portion. Those who minister to God\u2019s people and serve
          them are worthy of double honor. See  . Jesus is our heavenly Joshua who
          waits for the fullness of his inheritance until his people have received
          theirs. Receiving in us the fullness of his inheritance was the joy that
          was set before him (see  ). The church, his bride, is the \u201Ccity\u201D
          he desired. See  ;  ;  . He has built up this city and dwells there.  "
